snippet.title: Amber Heard Retracts Spousal Support Request
snippet.description:
Amber Heard has retracted her spousal support request.

Three weeks after filing for divorce from Johnny Depp, Amber¬ís attorney filed a declaration in order to withdraw Amber¬ís request for temporary spousal support.
In her original filing, Amber requested 50,000 dollars per month in spousal support, but that request was denied by a judge after she was granted a temporary restraining order against Johnny.
However, Amber says she asked for the spousal support because she thought it was standard procedure in divorce cases. She adds that the spousal support issue is being used against her to distract and divert the public away from the "very serious real issue of domestic violence."

snippet.title: Amber Laura Heard Biography Wiki, Husband, Age, Net Worth, Movie List
snippet.description:
Amber Laura Heard Biography Wiki, husband, Age, Instagram, Net Worth, Movie List
Video Link: https://youtu.be/M7R1iA8ZXls
Website Home URL : http://www.vneedy.com/
More Celebrity Biography  : http://www.vneedy.com/celebrities-biography/

Amber Laura Heard (born April 22, 1986) is an American film and television actress. After a series of small roles in film and television, Heard had her first starring role in the horror film All the Boys Love Mandy Lane (2006).
Heard was born in Austin, Texas, to Patricia Paige (n√©e Parsons), an internet researcher (1956‚Äì2020), and David Clinton Heard (born 1950), who owned a small construction company. She has a younger sister, Whitney. The family lived outside Austin.
Heard's earliest acting work included appearances in two music videos, Kenny Chesney's "There Goes My Life" and Eisley's "I Wasn't Prepared", and small supporting roles in the television series Jack & Bobby (2004), The Mountain (2004), and The O.C. (2005).
Heard is an American Civil Liberties Union (ACLU) ambassador to whom he donated her divorce settlement, and a Human Rights Champion for the Stand Up for Human Rights campaign by the Office of the United Nations High Commissioner for Human Rights.
Heard publicly came out in 2010, but has stated, "I don't label myself one way or another‚ÄîI have had successful relationships with men and now a woman. I love who I love; it's the person that matters." She was in a relationship with photographer Tasya van Ree from 2008 to 2012. In 2009, Heard was arrested in Washington for misdemeanor domestic violence, after allegedly grabbing van Ree and hitting her arm, but was never charged.
Heard and Depp began dating in 2012 and were married in a civil ceremony in February 2015. In April 2015, Heard breached Australia's biosecurity laws when she failed to declare her and Depp's two dogs to the customs when they flew into Queensland, where he was working on a film.

Amber Laura Heard (born April 22, 1986) is an American film and television actress. After a series of small roles in film and television, Heard had her first starring role in the horror film All the Boys Love Mandy Lane (2006).
Heard was born in Austin, Texas, to Patricia Paige (n√©e Parsons), an internet researcher (1956‚Äì2020), and David Clinton Heard (born 1950), who owned a small construction company. She has a younger sister, Whitney. The family lived outside Austin.
Heard's earliest acting work included appearances in two music videos, Kenny Chesney's "There Goes My Life" and Eisley's "I Wasn't Prepared", and small supporting roles in the television series Jack & Bobby (2004), The Mountain (2004), and The O.C. (2005).
Heard is an American Civil Liberties Union (ACLU) ambassador to whom he donated her divorce settlement, and a Human Rights Champion for the Stand Up for Human Rights campaign by the Office of the United Nations High Commissioner for Human Rights.
Heard publicly came out in 2010, but has stated, "I don't label myself one way or another‚ÄîI have had successful relationships with men and now a woman. I love who I love; it's the person that matters." She was in a relationship with photographer Tasya van Ree from 2008 to 2012. In 2009, Heard was arrested in Washington for misdemeanor domestic violence, after allegedly grabbing van Ree and hitting her arm, but was never charged.
Heard and Depp began dating in 2012 and were married in a civil ceremony in February 2015. In April 2015, Heard breached Australia's biosecurity laws when she failed to declare her and Depp's two dogs to the customs when they flew into Queensland, where he was working on a film.

snippet.title: Hearing on Johnny Depp domestic violence allegations delayed
snippet.description:
(10 Aug 2016) HEARING ON JOHNNY DEPP DOMESTIC VIOLENCE ALLEGATIONS DELAYED
A hearing on Amber Heard's allegations that Johnny Depp physically abused her is expected to last up to a week, prompting a judge Tuesday to delay its start.
Los Angeles Superior Court Judge Carl H. Moor ruled Tuesday that the hearing will begin Aug. 17, two days later than planned. Moor ordered the delay after concluding the hearing may take up to five days.
The domestic violence allegations are one aspect of the actors' contentious divorce. Heard filed to divorce Depp on May 23, and a few days later obtained a temporary restraining order after accusing the actor of repeatedly hitting her during a fight in their Los Angeles apartment.
Depp's lawyer has denied the allegations, and she said Tuesday he wants the hearing concluded as quickly as possible. "This is weighing heavily on my client," attorney Laura Wasser said.
If Heard prevails, the restraining order against Depp could be extended for up to five years.
Heard wants to call Depp as a hostile witness during the proceedings.
Moor ordered Heard to sit for a deposition on Friday and Depp to give sworn testimony in advance of the hearing on Saturday.
Depp will not be allowed to attend Heard's deposition, Moor ruled.
Heard accused Depp of repeatedly hitting her and throwing a cellphone during a fight in their Los Angeles apartment in May. A judge ordered Depp to not contact Heard and stay 100 yards away from her.
Los Angeles police responded to their apartment, but the person who made the call declined to file charges and officers determined no crime occurred.
Heard has alleged in court filings that Depp abuse throughout their relationship, which started after they met on the set of the 2011 film "The Rum Diary."

snippet.title: Amber Heard wears knitted vest at Cannes Film Festival
snippet.description: She was pictured keeping a low profile in a car with Heidi Klum's ex-boyfriend, art dealer, Vito Schnabel, on Tuesday.  And Amber Heard, 32, appeared in high spirits as she headed onto a boat in Cannes at the 71st annual Film Festival on Thursday.  She wore a knitted white vest top which was low-cut in design as she made her way down the promenade in 22 degree heat.  The number was tucked into a pair of high-waisted baggy trousers as she walked along with her hands tucked into her pockets.  Her blonde locks were styled into loose curls as she battled a little wind as she neared the water.  And she kindly posed for snaps with fans as she made the most of her day in the sunshine.  The night before, Amber wore a sensational gold knitted dress as she headed out in France, less than a day after being seen out with Vito, 31.  The Rum Diaries actress, who last dated entrepreneur Elon Musk and was married to Johnny Depp before that was seen in a car with Vito in New York on Tuesday.  The duo appeared deep in conversation while traveling somewhere in an SUV and ducked down out of sight after spotting onlookers.  Schnabel dated America's Got Talent star Klum, 44, off and on from 2014 until 2017.  Meanwhile, Amber's ex Elon Musk has a new lady in his life.  The Tesla founder made things official with musician Grimes as they graced Monday night's Met Gala in NYC.
